Q: What is tool chain? 

A: Set of programming tools that work together to build software from source code to an executable program

Main component usually has

1. Compiler

Convert source code into machine code / intermediate format

2. Assembler 

Translate assembly code into machine code 

3. Linker 

Combines multiple files and libs into a single executable

4. Libraries

Pre written code 

5. Debugger 

Help find and fix errors in program 

6. Other tools 

Sometimes includes build system, package managers, cross compiler for targeting different platform

